    "A key finding of this study is the central role of the Knit in structuring the whole framework, whereas the Nerve turns out to be functorial only on some restricted domains.",
    "In the opposite direction, the functor Canon is introduced; it associates to any political formation its canonical political site.",
    "Since the Knit of the canonical site of a formation is precisely this very formation, the functor Canon has the Knit as a left inverse.",
    "Any transformation that occurs in a political site is reflected in a recomposition of the political formation and conversely any observable recomposition of a political formation can be attributed to some transformation of some political site.In this part of the study, there is an important restriction concerning admissible transformations and recompositions: in formal terms our mor-phisms are built on functionsfoot_0; this amounts to admit only recompositions that represent union of parties of the Base and modifications that represent merger of states of the Ground.The paper is organized as follows.",
    "The first section, devoted to the objects of our categories, introduces the notions of p-site and p-formation."
